## Featured Research

```{=html}
<div class="project-card">
  <h3>Reproducible Data Science Pipeline for HIV Epidemiology &mdash; Children &amp; Adolescents</h3>
  <div class="project-tags">
    <span class="tag">HIV Epidemiology</span>
    <span class="tag">R</span>
    <span class="tag">Docker</span>
    <span class="tag">GitHub</span>
    <span class="tag">Reproducible Research</span>
    <span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
  </div>
  <p>HIV continues to disproportionately affect children and adolescents globally, yet granular, reproducible analyses of long-term trends are scarce. This project built an end-to-end reproducible data analysis pipeline using UNAIDS HIV epidemiology data for children and adolescents aged 0&ndash;19, covering the years 2000&ndash;2020.</p>
  <p>The pipeline automates every step from data ingestion to publication-ready output: descriptive epidemiologic analysis, time-trend visualization of HIV incidence, and automated report generation using Makefile-driven workflows. The entire analytical environment was containerized using Docker to ensure cross-platform reproducibility, and dependency management with renv locks R package versions for consistent results. A validated public Docker Hub image allows anyone to fully reproduce all results with a single command.</p>
