    <i class="fab fa-github"></i> View on GitHub
  </a>
</div>

<div class="project-card">
  <h3>Capstone Research: Routine Immunization Disruptions &amp; Vaccine-Preventable Disease Trends</h3>
  <div class="project-tags">
    <span class="tag">Epidemiology</span>
    <span class="tag">Immunization</span>
    <span class="tag">Surveillance Data</span>
    <span class="tag">CARE</span>
    <span class="tag">Global Health</span>
  </div>
  <p>Disruptions to routine immunization programs can have serious downstream consequences for vaccine-preventable disease (VPD) burden. This capstone project analyzed surveillance and immunization datasets across CARE-supported governorates to evaluate changes in VPD incidence between 2024 and 2025.</p>
  <p>The analysis assessed ecological associations between measles incidence and measles-rubella vaccination delivery using facility-level data, and examined trends across 399 VPD cases spanning measles, mumps, pertussis, hepatitis A/B, and chickenpox. Findings were synthesized into an epidemiologic report and poster presentation, providing actionable insights for immunization program planning and disease prevention strategy.</p>
