## Research Experience Projects

```{=html}
<div class="project-card">
  <h3>HIV Stigma Metrics Repository &mdash; CHIMES, Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health</h3>
  <div class="project-tags">
    <span class="tag">HIV Stigma</span>
    <span class="tag">Psychometrics</span>
    <span class="tag">R</span>
    <span class="tag">Systematic Review</span>
    <span class="tag">Johns Hopkins</span>
  </div>
  <p>HIV-related stigma remains one of the most significant barriers to testing, treatment, and care engagement. As part of a prestigious Applied Practice Experience at Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health (ranked #1 globally), this project developed an expanded, robust repository of attribute-specific and intersectional HIV stigma metrics.</p>
  <p>Working with the Center for HIV and Mental Health Stigma Elimination Strategies (CHIMES), reproducible R pipelines were designed and implemented for psychometric validation of HIV-related stigma scales across multiple populations. The work included computing descriptive statistics, item distributions, and Cronbach's alpha for large survey datasets, and executing systematic literature searches across PubMed, Embase, CINAHL, and PsycINFO using MeSH and Emtree terms.</p>
</div>

<div class="project-card">
  <h3>U.S. PrEP Locator Database Maintenance &mdash; PRISM HIV Prevention Team, Emory</h3>
  <div class="project-tags">
    <span class="tag">HIV Prevention</span>
    <span class="tag">PrEP</span>
    <span class="tag">HRSA-Funded</span>
    <span class="tag">Data Management</span>
    <span class="tag">Public Health</span>
  </div>
  <p>Access to pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) is critical for HIV prevention, yet provider availability varies widely across the United States. As a Graduate Research Assistant with the PRISM HIV Prevention Team at Emory's Department of Epidemiology, this work involves maintaining and updating the U.S. PrEP Locator — a national provider-access directory covering 3,000+ providers nationwide.</p>
  <p>This role ensures data accuracy and improved accessibility of HIV prevention services for individuals and providers across the country, directly supporting an HRSA-funded initiative to reduce HIV burden in underserved communities.</p>
</div>

<div class="project-card">
  <h3>Epidemiologic Profiling &amp; Pharmaceutical Portfolio Strategy &mdash; Zydus Lifesciences (U.S. Market)</h3>
  <div class="project-tags">
    <span class="tag">Pharmaceutical Epidemiology</span>
    <span class="tag">Competitive Intelligence</span>
    <span class="tag">U.S. Market</span>
    <span class="tag">Portfolio Strategy</span>
  </div>
  <p>Understanding the epidemiologic landscape of a disease is foundational to effective pharmaceutical strategy. In this role at Zydus Lifesciences, epidemiologic profiles were developed for 25+ therapeutic indications in the U.S. market, covering disease burden, treatment algorithms, competitive pipelines, and unmet needs.</p>
  <p>The work included evaluating quarterly pipelines of ~45 branded companies to identify early-stage products for development and label expansion, monitoring ANDA and NDA approvals, and mapping competitive landscapes to inform R&D strategy. This experience bridges the worlds of epidemiology, pharmaceutical science, and strategic business intelligence.</p>
</div>
